  <description><![CDATA[<p>The Hotel Rodella's has a stunning location on the outskirts of <a data-udi="umb://document/37d9070a8d4e4a609b9c192e453f0f97" href="/{localLink:umb://document/37d9070a8d4e4a609b9c192e453f0f97}" title="Selva">Selva,</a> with amazing views over the valley and mountains. The Planker family have run the hotel for generations and are extremely welcoming and informative. Get chatting and if you're lucky you may get to join one of their weekly wine tastings in the cellar!</p>
<h2>Idyllic location</h2>
<p>Set on a hill on the outskirts of Selva, the hotel enjoys a peaceful location with incredible views of the Val Gardena - look out for the Sella massif to the east, the spectacular Sassolungo to the south and the Pic to the north.</p>
<p>The centre of town is about a kilometre away but there are plenty of options available to get you there and back. Jump on the hotel's free shuttle to and from the lifts or use the free local bus which runs every half an hour at peak times. If the conditions are good, you can even ski straight to the Santa Cristina lift.</p>
<h2>Fabulous food and drink</h2>
<p>The real star of the show is the food. The hotel have been awarded the ‘Gambero Rosso award’ for exceptional Italian food and wine. A varied breakfast buffet is served each day with hot and cold options available.</p>
<p>Dinner is served in the lovely dining area, where you can enjoy a four course meal and each week you can taste some Tyrolean specialities with local cheeses and wine. Take in the incredible mountain views with a drink or two at the hotel bar - it is the ideal spot to enjoy an aperitif before dinner or a nightcap. </p>
<h2>Soothing spa and relaxation</h2>
<p>The rest of the hotel is special too. The bedrooms are furnished in a modern Tyrolean style, and benefit from having a balcony with mountain views, so you can watch the world go by from the comfort of your room. </p>
<p>Take a moment to enjoy the spa and wellness area. Take a dip in the panoramic indoor pool, and enjoy views of the village, relax in the jacuzzies, unwind in the sauna or steam room, or soak up the winter sun on the terrace. Massages and treatments are available for a local fee. </p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Hotel Rodella the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>]]></description>
